---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Real Estate Commission Calculator — Free Agent & Broker Split Tool" description="Calculate real estate agent commission, broker splits, and net pay instantly. Free tool for buyers, sellers, and agents.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-center">Real Estate Commission Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-center mb-10">Calculate agent commission, broker split, and net earnings for any sale price.</p>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
        <div>
          <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Sale Price ($)</label>
          <input type="number" id="salePrice" value="450000" min="0" step="1000"
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Total Commission Rate (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="commissionRate" value="5.5" min="0" max="10" step="0.1"
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Buyer's Agent Split (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="buyerSplit" value="50" min="0" max="100" step="1"
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Agent/Broker Split (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="agentBrokerSplit" value="70" min="0" max="100" step="1"
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="results" class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mt-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 text-center border border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Total Commission</p>
          <p id="totalComm" class="text-xl font-bold text-indigo-700">$24,750</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 text-center border border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Listing Agent Gets</p>
          <p id="listingAgent" class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600">$8,663</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 text-center border border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Buyer's Agent Gets</p>
          <p id="buyerAgent" class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600">$8,663</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 text-center border border-gray-100">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Seller's Net (after comm.)</p>
          <p id="sellerNet" class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-700">$425,250</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>How Real Estate Commissions Work</h2>
      <p>In the US, real estate commissions are typically 5–6% of the sale price, split between the listing agent and buyer's agent. Each agent then splits their portion with their brokerage.</p>
      <h3>The 2024 NAR Settlement Impact</h3>
      <p>Following the NAR settlement, buyer's agent commissions are now negotiated separately and must be agreed upon in writing before touring homes. This has led to more varied commission structures.</p>
      <h3>Typical Commission Splits</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>New agents:</strong> 50/50 with broker</li>
        <li><strong>Experienced agents:</strong> 70/30 to 80/20</li>
        <li><strong>Top producers:</strong> 90/10 or 100% (desk fee model)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    function fmt(n) { return '$' + Math.round(n).toLocaleString('en-US'); }
    function calc() {
      const price = parseFloat(document.getElementById('salePrice').value) || 0;
      const rate = parseFloat(document.getElementById('commissionRate').value) / 100 || 0;
      const buyerPct = parseFloat(document.getElementById('buyerSplit').value) / 100 || 0.5;
      const agentPct = parseFloat(document.getElementById('agentBrokerSplit').value) / 100 || 0.7;
      const total = price * rate;
      const listingPool = total * (1 - buyerPct);
      const buyerPool = total * buyerPct;
      const listingAgentNet = listingPool * agentPct;
      const buyerAgentNet = buyerPool * agentPct;
      document.getElementById('totalComm').textContent = fmt(total);
      document.getElementById('listingAgent').textContent = fmt(listingAgentNet);
      document.getElementById('buyerAgent').textContent = fmt(buyerAgentNet);
      document.getElementById('sellerNet').textContent = fmt(price - total);
    }
    document.querySelectorAll('input').forEach(el => el.addEventListener('input', calc));
    calc();
  </script>
</Base>
